org.universAAL.middleware.rdf

Class ClosedCollection

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractList<E>
        • java.util.ArrayList
          • org.universAAL.middleware.rdf.ObjectCollection
            • org.universAAL.middleware.rdf.ClosedCollection
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, Iterable, Collection, List, RandomAccess

    public final class ClosedCollection
extends ObjectCollection
    Class for handling multiple values of a property in RDF. As compared to OpenCollection, the ClosedCollection defines that the collection of objects is closed, i.e. there can not be more objects. Example: If you have some sensors in a room that can determine the exact set of persons in a room and you know that no one else can be there then you can express this with a ClosedCollection, e.g. the LivingRoom contains exactly the people {Joe, Juan}.
    Author:
    Carsten Stockloew
    See Also:
    OpenCollection, Serialized Form
